## 5. Implementation Steps

### Domain Layer
- [x] Create `InvoiceStatus` enum (`Draft`, `Sent`, `Paid`, `Cancelled`)
- [x] Create `Customer` aggregate root with properties: `Name`, `Email`, `Phone`, `Address`; include a navigation collection `Invoices` (for EF config only ‚Äî not used in domain logic)
- [x] Create `InvoiceItem` entity owned by `Invoice` with: `Description`, `Quantity`, `UnitPrice`, `LineTotal` (computed: `Quantity √ó UnitPrice`)
- [x] Create `Invoice` aggregate root with: `InvoiceNumber`, `CustomerId`, `IssueDate`, `DueDate`, `Status`, `Notes`, `TotalAmount`, and `Items` collection; add domain methods `AddItem(...)`, `RemoveItem(Guid itemId)`, and `CalculateTotal()` that sums `LineTotal` of all items

### Application Contracts Layer
- [x] Define `CustomerDto` and `CreateUpdateCustomerDto` (with `[Required]` / `[MaxLength]` data annotations)
- [x] Define `InvoiceDto` (includes `CustomerName`, `List<InvoiceItemDto>`, `TotalAmount`), `CreateUpdateInvoiceDto`, `InvoiceItemDto`, `CreateUpdateInvoiceItemDto`, `GetInvoiceListInput`
- [x] Define `ICustomerAppService` extending `ICrudAppService<...>`
- [x] Define `IInvoiceAppService` with `GetListAsync`, `GetAsync`, `CreateAsync`, `UpdateAsync`, `DeleteAsync`, `AddItemAsync`, `UpdateItemAsync`, `RemoveItemAsync`
- [x] Add `Customers` and `Invoices` nested permission groups to `QuickBillsPermissions` following the pattern `QuickBills.Customers.Create`, `QuickBills.Customers.Edit`, etc.
- [x] Register all permissions in `QuickBillsPermissionDefinitionProvider`

### Application Layer
- [x] Implement `CustomerAppService` using `CrudAppService` base ‚Äî requires only AutoMapper + permission policy names
- [x] Implement `InvoiceAppService`: list query uses `GetQueryableAsync()` with `Include(i => i.Items)` and `AsNoTracking()`; single-entity fetch uses `WithDetailsAsync(i => i.Items)`; `AddItemAsync`/`RemoveItemAsync` load the tracked aggregate and call domain methods; all write operations are authorized with the corresponding permission
- [x] Add AutoMapper profiles for all entity ‚Üí DTO mappings in `QuickBillsApplicationAutoMapperProfile.cs`

### Infrastructure Layer
- [x] Create separate `IEntityTypeConfiguration<T>` classes for `Customer`, `Invoice`, and `InvoiceItem`; configure table names using `QuickBillsConsts.DbTablePrefix` (`AppCustomers`, `AppInvoices`, `AppInvoiceItems`), call `b.ConfigureByConvention()`, define the `Invoice ‚Üí InvoiceItems` one-to-many with `HasForeignKey` + `OnDelete(DeleteBehavior.Cascade)`
- [x] Register configurations in `OnModelCreating` via `builder.ApplyConfiguration(...)` and expose `DbSet<Customer>`, `DbSet<Invoice>`, `DbSet<InvoiceItem>`
- [x] Add and apply EF Core migration for SQLite

### Blazor UI Layer
- [x] Add localization keys in `en.json` for all page titles, column headers, button labels, and validation messages (e.g., `"Menu:Customers"`, `"Customers"`, `"NewCustomer"`, `"Invoices"`, `"InvoiceNumber"`, `"TotalAmount"`, etc.)
- [x] Add `QuickBillsMenus.Customers` and `QuickBillsMenus.Invoices` constants; register both as top-level menu items in `QuickBillsMenuContributor` with permission guards (`RequirePermissions(QuickBillsPermissions.Customers.Default)`)
- [x] Build `/customers` page: paginated `AbpDataGrid` (or table) with columns Name, Email, Phone; inline Create/Edit modal using `AbpModal`; delete with confirmation; authorize actions with Customer permissions
- [x] Build `/invoices` list page: table with Invoice Number, Customer Name, Issue Date, Due Date, Status badge, Total Amount; link each row to the detail page; Create modal for new invoices (customer dropdown populated from `ICustomerAppService.GetListAsync`)
- [x] Build `/invoices/{id}` detail page: invoice header info + status; read-only summary of Customer; editable `InvoiceItems` table (Add / Edit / Remove item inline); display computed `TotalAmount` that refreshes after every item mutation

### Authorization wiring
- [x] Ensure every AppService method is decorated with `[Authorize(QuickBillsPermissions.Xxx.Yyy)]`
- [x] Ensure Blazor pages hide/disable Create, Edit, Delete buttons when the user lacks the corresponding permission (use `IAuthorizationService` or ABP's `<AbpPermissionCheck>`)

